def createSpectrogram(path, divided, segment):
  y, sr = librosa.load(path)

  if(divided == True):
    samplesPerTrack = 22050 * 30
    samplesPerSegment = int(samplesPerTrack / 5)
    spectrogramsPerSegment = math.ceil(samplesPerSegment / 512)

    start = samplesPerSegment * segment
    finish = start + samplesPerSegment
    y = y[start:finish]
    
  spect = librosa.feature.melspectrogram(
      y=y, sr=sr, n_mels=128, n_fft=2048, hop_length=512)
  
  spect = librosa.core.pcen(
      spect, sr=sr, hop_length=512, gain=0.6, bias=0.1,
      power=0.2, time_constant=0.4, eps=1e-9)
    
  #spect = librosa.power_to_db(spect, ref=np.max)

  return spect.T

def createMFCC(path, divided, segment):
  y, sr = librosa.load(path)

  if(divided == True):
    samplesPerTrack = 22050 * 30
    samplesPerSegment = int(samplesPerTrack / 5)
    spectrogramsPerSegment = math.ceil(samplesPerSegment / 512)

    start = samplesPerSegment * segment
    finish = start + samplesPerSegment
    y = y[start:finish]
  
  mfcc = librosa.feature.mfcc(
      y=y, sr=sr, n_fft=2048, hop_length=512)
    
  #spect = librosa.power_to_db(spect, ref=np.max)

  return mfcc.T

def load(filepath):

    filename = os.path.basename(filepath)

    if 'features' in filename:
        return pd.read_csv(filepath, index_col=0, header=[0, 1, 2])

    if 'echonest' in filename:
        return pd.read_csv(filepath, index_col=0, header=[0, 1, 2])

    if 'genres' in filename:
        return pd.read_csv(filepath, index_col=0)

    if 'tracks' in filename:
        tracks = pd.read_csv(filepath, index_col=0, header=[0, 1])

        COLUMNS = [('track', 'tags'), ('album', 'tags'), ('artist', 'tags'),
                   ('track', 'genres'), ('track', 'genres_all')]
        for column in COLUMNS:
            tracks[column] = tracks[column].map(ast.literal_eval)

        COLUMNS = [('track', 'date_created'), ('track', 'date_recorded'),
                   ('album', 'date_created'), ('album', 'date_released'),
                   ('artist', 'date_created'), ('artist', 'active_year_begin'),
                   ('artist', 'active_year_end')]
        for column in COLUMNS:
            tracks[column] = pd.to_datetime(tracks[column])

        SUBSETS = ('small', 'medium', 'large')
        try:
            tracks['set', 'subset'] = tracks['set', 'subset'].astype(
                    'category', categories=SUBSETS, ordered=True)
        except (ValueError, TypeError):
            # the categories and ordered arguments were removed in pandas 0.25
            tracks['set', 'subset'] = tracks['set', 'subset'].astype(
                     pd.CategoricalDtype(categories=SUBSETS, ordered=True))

        COLUMNS = [('track', 'genre_top'), ('track', 'license'),
                   ('album', 'type'), ('album', 'information'),
                   ('artist', 'bio')]
        for column in COLUMNS:
            tracks[column] = tracks[column].astype('category')

        return tracks

mainDirectory = [directory for directory in listdir(music_dir) if isdir(join(music_dir, directory))]
mainDirectory.sort()

filePaths = []

for directory in mainDirectory:
  musicFiles = [fileName for fileName in listdir(join(music_dir, directory))]
  
  for mf in musicFiles:
    filePaths.append(music_dir + directory + "/" + mf)

print(filePaths)

spectrograms = np.empty((0, 640, 128))
 
i = 0

validSpecs = genreIDs.copy()

for path in filePaths:
    with warnings.catch_warnings():
        try:
            warnings.simplefilter("ignore")
            spect = createSpectrogram(path)
            spect = spect[:640, :]
            spectrograms = np.append(spectrograms, [spect], axis=0)
        except:
            removed = validSpecs.pop(i)
            print("REMOVED: %s at index %s" % (str(removed), str(i)))
            
            if(i > 0):
                i -= 1

    i += 1

validSpecs = np.array(validSpecs)

print("%s processed" % str(i))
np.save("C:/Users/twelveWings/Documents/Python/Final_Project/fma_X_spec.npy", spectrograms)
np.save("C:/Users/twelveWings/Documents/Python/Final_Project/fma_y_spec.npy", validSpecs)

inputShape = (None,  128)
inputLayer = Input(shape=inputShape)

#Input Layer
layer = inputLayer

# Convolutional Layers
for i in range(3):
  layer = Conv1D(filters=3, kernel_size=5)(layer)
  layer = BatchNormalization(momentum=0.9)(layer)
  layer = Activation('relu')(layer)
  layer = MaxPooling1D(2)(layer)

# LSTM Layer
layer = LSTM(96, return_sequences=True)(layer)
layer = LSTM(64)(layer)

# Fully connected layer
layer = Dense(32)(layer)
layer = Dense(8)(layer)
layer = Activation('softmax')(layer)

pred = layer

model = Model(inputs=inputLayer, outputs=pred)

opt = RMSprop(lr=0.00075)

model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy', optimizer=opt, metrics=['accuracy'])

model.summary()

def show_summary_stats(history):
    # List all data in history
    print(history.history.keys())

    # Summarize history for accuracy
    plt.plot(history.history['accuracy'])
    plt.plot(history.history['val_accuracy'])
    plt.title('model accuracy')
    plt.ylabel('accuracy')
    plt.xlabel('epoch')
    plt.legend(['train', 'test'], loc='upper left')
    plt.show()

    # Summarize history for loss
    plt.plot(history.history['loss'])
    plt.plot(history.history['val_loss'])
    plt.title('model loss')
    plt.ylabel('loss')
    plt.xlabel('epoch')
    plt.legend(['train', 'test'], loc='upper left')
    plt.show()

show_summary_stats(history)

mfcc = np.empty((0, 640, 20))
 
i = 0

for path in filePaths:
    with warnings.catch_warnings():
        try:
            warnings.simplefilter("ignore")
            coefficient = createMFCC(path)
            coefficient = coefficient[:640, :]
            mfcc = np.append(mfcc, [coefficient], axis=0)
        except:
            removed = genreIDs.pop(i)
            print("REMOVED: %s at index %s" % (str(removed), str(i)))
            
            if(i > 0):
                i -= 1

    i += 1

print("%s processed" % str(i))

inputShape = (None,  20)
inputLayer = Input(shape=inputShape)

#Input Layer
layer = inputLayer

# Convolutional Layers
for i in range(3):
  layer = Conv1D(filters=3, kernel_size=5)(layer)
  layer = BatchNormalization(momentum=0.9)(layer)
  layer = Activation('relu')(layer)
  layer = MaxPooling1D(2)(layer)

# LSTM Layer
layer = LSTM(96, return_sequences=False)(layer)

# Fully connected layer
layer = Dense(64)(layer)
layer = Dense(8)(layer)
layer = Activation('softmax')(layer)

pred = layer

model = Model(inputs=inputLayer, outputs=pred)

opt = RMSprop(lr=0.00075)

model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy', optimizer=opt, metrics=['accuracy'])

model.summary()
